jparsec.ephem.moons

Class GUST86

  • java.lang.Object
    • jparsec.ephem.moons.GUST86

  • public class GUST86
extends java.lang.Object
    A class to obtain the position of the satellites of Uranus. Objects are Miranda, Ariel, Umbriel, Titania, and Oberon.

    For reference see: GUST86 - An analytical ephemeris of the Uranian satellites, Laskar J., Jacobson, R., Astron. Astrophys. 188, 212-224 (1987).

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    T. Alonso Albi - OAN (Spain)

      • GUST86_theory

        public static double[] GUST86_theory(double TJJ,
                     int IS,
                     int ICODE)
        GUST86 theory. Output array depends on the value of ICODE.
        Parameters:
        TJJ - Julian day in TDB.
        IS - Satellite ID, from 1 (Miranda) to 5 (Oberon).
        ICODE - Output format. 1 for eliptic elements B1950, 2 for uranocentric vector J1950 refered to Uranus equator, 3 for uranocentric equatorial vector J1950, 4 for the same as 3 in B1950.
        Returns:
        Array with (x, y, z, vx, vy, vz), or with the 6 eliptic elements:

        SEMIMAJOR AXIS (KM).

        LONGITUDE (RD).

        K=E*COS(PI).

        H=E*SIN(PI).

        Q=SIN(I/2)*COS(GOM).

        P=SIN(I/2)*SIN(GOM).

        E : ECCENTRICITY.

        PI : LONGITUDE OF PERIASTRE.

        I : INCLINATION.

        GOM : ASCENDING NODE LONGITUDE.
